Package my.example.code

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    DataCenterInstances
    Describes a set of behaviors used for storing data center capacity data and calculating the usable machine groups (M) the data describes.
    DataCenterInstancesReader<D extends DataCenterInstances>
    Describes a set of behaviors used for reading in data center capacity data.
    DataSubsetGroup
    Describes a set of behaviors used for storing and manipulating the set of all instances holding a single data subset (spans machine groups).
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DataCenterCapacity
    Implementation of a data center capacity exercise for the Apple Search Engineering team interview process.
    DataSubsetVersion
    Provides a factory for wrappers of int versions.
    FileDataCenterInstancesReader<D extends DataCenterInstances>
    Implementation of a set of behaviors used for reading in data center capacity data from a file.
    StandardInDataCenterInstancesReader<D extends DataCenterInstances>
    Implementation of a set of behaviors used for reading in data center capacity data from standard input.
    UniqueVersionsDataCenterInstances
    Implements a set of behaviors used for storing data center capacity data and calculating the usable machine groups (M) the data describes.
    UniqueVersionsDataSubsetGroup
    Implementation of DataSubsetGroup that maintains the set of unique versions found in this data subset and the count of machine instances that are using each of these versions.
